data.enText: to do or be better than sb/sth

data.chText: 他希望有一天能刷新世界纪录。
data.enText: He hopes one day to surpass the world record.

data.chText: 它所取得的成功远远超出了预期。
data.enText: Its success has surpassed all expectations .

data.chText: 她的厨艺向来不错，但这一次她更是胜过以往。
data.enText: Her cooking was always good, but this time she had surpassed herself (= done better than her own high standards) .

simple_means.memory_skill: sur 上；超；外加 + pass 通过 → 超过

ex.enText: Tom was exceeding the speed limit.

ex.chText: 工作时间每天不得超过8小时。
ex.enText: Working hours must not exceed 8 hours a day.

synonyms.bx: 指超越职权范围、法律规定等，或超出数量、程度、大小等。

ex.chText: 她在舞蹈方面出类拔萃。

synonyms.bx: 通常指在成就、学识等方面胜过他人，不用进行时。

ex.chText: 中国将在经济上超过日本。
ex.enText: China will surpass Japan in economy.

synonyms.bx: 指在技能、成就等方面超越同类。

tr: be or do something to a greater degree
example: her performance surpasses that of any other student I know
This car outperforms all others in its class
A black limousine passed by when she looked out the window
He passed his professor in the hall
One line of soldiers surpassed the other

tr: be greater in scope or size than some standard
example: Their loyalty exceeds their national bonds

value.def: If one person or thing surpasses another, the first is better than, or has more of a particular quality than, the second.

example.ex: He was determined to surpass the achievements of his older brothers...
example.tran: 他决心超越几个哥哥的成就。

example.ex: Warwick Arts Centre is the second largest Arts Centre in Britain, surpassed in size only by London's Barbican.
example.tran: 沃里克艺术中心是英国第二大艺术中心，规模仅次于伦敦的巴比肯。

value.def: If something surpasses expectations, it is much better than it was expected to be.

example.ex: Conrad Black gave an excellent party that surpassed expectations.
example.tran: 康拉德·布莱克举办了一次远超人们预期的精彩聚会。

value.def: If something surpasses understanding, it is too difficult to understand.

example.ex: ...a clever and spectacularly successful system, the detailed complexity of which surpasses our full understanding.
example.tran: 一个设计巧妙且极其成功的系统，其复杂的细节非我辈所能完全理解
